                        },
                        "dcterms:description": "Soprano is a Python library to help scientists working with crystallography and simulations to generate, manipulate, run calculations on and analyse large data sets of crystal structures. It provides a number of functionalities to help automate many common tasks in computational crystallography, including NMR parameter manipulation. Documentation and tutorials are provided to help users get started with the library.",
