                        "@type": "psdiDcatExt:Guidance",
                        "dcterms:title": "Mini-Tutorials for XAFS RO-Crate Workflows in Galaxy",
                        "rdfs:label": "Mini-Tutorials for XAFS RO-Crate Workflows in Galaxy",
                        "dcterms:type": {
                            "skos:prefLabel": "Text",
                            "@type": "skos:Concept",
                            "@id": "http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/Text"
                        },
                        "dcterms:description": "The Mini-Tutorials for XAFS RO-Crate Workflows in Galaxy provide a brief introduction to working with RO-Crates in Galaxy. The development of the tutorials originated as quickstart guidance for running and inspecting workflows used for the reproduction of X-ray absorption fine structure (XAFS) analyses. These self-paced learning resources cover three aspects of the RO-Crate lifecycle in the Galaxy platform: Importing (and running) a workflow, Creation (Exporting) an RO-Crate and Importing (and inspecting) an RO-Crate.",
