                    },
                    "dcterms:description": "Data-to-Knowledge Collections provide curated datasets specifically designed for use in machine learning or generated through machine learning processes. An example is the Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials (MLIPs) data collection, which includes MLIP XYZ files used for training, the trained MLIP models, and, where available, additional metadata such as AIIDA provenance information. By making these datasets accessible, researchers without the resources to generate such data themselves can leverage them for machine learning. Additionally, the MLIP models can be directly applied in modeling tasks, enabling broader exploration and advancements in research.",
