                    "@type": "psdiDcatExt:Tool",
                    "dcterms:title": "TopoStats: Batch Processing Atomic Force Microscopy (AFM) Images",
                    "rdfs:label": "TopoStats",
                    "dcterms:type": {
                        "skos:prefLabel": "Software",
                        "@type": "skos:Concept",
                        "@id": "http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/Software"
                    },
                    "dcterms:description": "TopoStats is a Python toolkit that automates the processing and analysis of Atomic Force Microscopy (AFM) data. It batch processes raw AFM files to identify molecules or other features, trace their shapes, and generate image outputs at each stage of the workflow. The software produces rich quantitative measurements in both tabular and graphical formats, and is developed in line with FAIR research software principles to support transparent, reproducible AFM analysis.",
